'''''Death Bringer''''', alternatively titled '''''Galdregon's Domain''''' in Europe, is a 1988 [[role-playing video game]] originally developed and self-published by [[Pandora (Interceptor Software)|Pandora]] and released for the [[Amiga]], [[Atari ST]], [[Commodore 64]], [[TurboGrafx-16#TurboGrafx-CD/CD-ROM²|TurboGrafx-CD]], and [[Sharp X68000]].

==Plot==
[[File:Death_Bringer_1988_Amiga_Gameplay_Screenshot.png|thumb|left|Combat is turn-based.]]

The game is set in the fictional world of Mezron, where a wizard by the name of Azazeal has been resurrected and is searching for the five gems of Zator. The player takes control of a warrior charged with recovering the jewels by battling many minions who guard them, such as [[Medusa]] and High Priestess Set. They then venture into the [[catacombs]] of Castle Secnar and battle the [[undead]].

